<h2>Economic & Development Statistics</h2><p>
	<div id="column2_text" class="scrollable">
	      <a href="http://www.igc.org.uk/en/default.aspx">International Grains Council</a> - Grain markets report. <br>
          <a href="http://comtrade.un.org/db/">UN Comtrade Database</a> - Searchable commodity trade statistics database. <br>
          <a href="http://archive.unctad.org/templates/Page.asp?intItemID=1584&lang=1">UNCTAD Commodity Price Statistics</a> - &quot;Monthly free-market prices and price indices starting in January 1960 for selected commodities that concern commodity-dependent countries. Price indices are provided for commodity groups (including food, tropical beverages, vegetable oilseeds and oils, agricultural raw materials, minerals, ores and metals), and for all groups in current dollars and SDRs.&quot; <br>
          <a href="http://www.unido.org/doc/50215.htmls">UN Industrial Development Organization (UNIDO)</a> - Economic indicators by country including statistics on manufacturing. <br>
          <a href="http://www.fas.usda.gov/commodities.asp">USDA Foreign Agricultural Service: Commodities and Products</a> - Links to US and international data. <br>
          <a href="http://minerals.usgs.gov/minerals/pubs/commodity/">USGS Minerals Information: Commodity Statistics and Information</a> - &quot;Statistics and information on the worldwide supply of, demand for, and flow of minerals and materials essential to the U.S. economy, the national security, and protection of the environment.&quot; <br>
          <a href="http://www.cid.harvard.edu/ciddata/">Center for International Development (CID) at Harvard University</a> - Data depository which includes the Highly Indebted Poor Countries (HIPC) Database, Trade Openness Indicators, Sources of Slow Growth in African Economies, Natural Resource Abundance and Economic Growth, plus geography, education, agricultural and disease datasets (most in  Excel format.) <br>
          <a href="http://sedac.ciesin.columbia.edu/povmap/">Global Distribution of Poverty</a> - Subnational, spatially explicit, poverty data sets. These are available for selected proxy measures of poverty, at global and national scales. <br>
          <a href="http://mdgs.un.org/unsd/mdg/Default.aspx">Millennium Development Goals Indicators</a> - This site presents the official data, definitions, methodologies and sources for more than 60 indicators to measure progress towards the United Nations Millennium Development Goals. Keyword searchable. <br>
          <a href="http://www.oecd.org/statisticsdata/0,2643,en_2649_34447_1_119656_1_1_1,00.html">OECD Aid Statistics</a> - Statistics and reports on aid and other resource flows to developing countries and countries in transition and related matters. <br>
          <a href="http://www.undp.org/publications/">United Nations Development Programme (UNDP)</a> - Human Development Report, Human Development Index, Gender-Related Development Index, Gender Empowerment Measure, Trends in Economic Performance, Financial Inflows and Outflows, Human Profile and Index, North-South Gaps, etc. <br>
          <a href="http://data.worldbank.org/">World Bank Development Data</a> - Includes World Development Reports, quick reference tables, Gas and Diesel Price Databank, Global Development Finance, and selected tables from World Development Indicators. <br>
          <a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/index.htm">Bank for International Settlements (BIS)</a> - Publications which can be downloaded include the Annual Report, &quot;Quarterly Review: International Banking and Financial Market Developments,&quot; &quot;BIS Consolidated International Banking Statistics,&quot; and &quot;Joint BIS-IMF-OECD-World Bank Statistics on External Debt.&quot; <br>
          <a href="http://www.bea.gov/International/Index.htm">Bureau of Economic Analysis International Accounts Data</a> - Statistics on balances and payments, imports and exports, investment position, foreign direct investment in the US, and US direct investment abroad. <br>
          <a href="http://www.federalreserve.gov/releases/">Federal Reserve Board</a> - Current and historical data on foreign exchange rates. <br>
          <a href="http://www.imf.org/">International Monetary Fund</a> - The most recent &quot;World Economic Outlook,&quot; Staff  Country Reports, Annual Report, IMF Working Papers, Summary of Disbursements and Repayments, and IMF Surveys. <br>
          <a href="http://archive.unctad.org/Templates/Page.asp?intItemID=4979&lang=1">UNCTAD Foreign Direct Investment Database</a> - &quot;The FDI database presents aggregate inflows, outflows, inward stocks and outward stocks of foreign direct investment (FDI) for 196 reporting economies in an interactive format.&quot; <br>
          <a href="http://unctad.org/en/Pages/DIAE/Investment%20and%20Enterprise/World-Investment-Directory.aspx">UNCTAD  World Investment Directory</a> - &quot;Detailed statistics on foreign direct investment (FDI) and operations of transnational corporations (TNCs) in selected countries.&quot; <br>
          <a href="http://stats.bls.gov/fls/home.htm">Foreign Labor Statistics</a> - Bureau of Labor Statistics data series. <br>
          <a href="http://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/">International Labour Organisation (ILO) Labour Statistics</a> - International labor statistics for many nations from 1988 -, including an International Labour Migration database. <br>
          <a href="http://www.bls.gov/mxp/home.htm">Bureau of Labor Statistics Import/Export Price Indexes</a> - &quot;The International Price Program produces Import Price Indexes (MPI) and Export Price Indexes (XPI) containing data on changes in the  prices of nonmilitary goods and services traded between the U.S. and the rest of the world.&quot; <br>
          <a href="http://www.export.gov/mrktresearch/index.asp">Export.gov</a> - Access to the U.S. Commercial Service Market Research Library: Country Commercial Guides, Market Updates, Industry Overviews, Multilateral Development Bank Reports, Best Markets, Industry/Regional Reports, and agricultural goods market research  reports. <br>
          <a href="http://www.census.gov/ftp/pub/foreign-trade/www/">Foreign Trade  Statistics</a> - US Census Bureau. Country-commodity trade data, trade balances with partner countries, and monthly lists of top trading partners. <br>
          <a href="http://www.ita.doc.gov/">International Trade Administration</a> - Office of Trade and Economic Analysis site has links to information to the US Industry and Trade Outlook, US Foreign Trade  Highlights, and Global Data Links. Free registration required. <br>
          <a href="http://web.worldbank.org/WBSITE/EXTERNAL/TOPICS/EXTTRANSPORT/EXTTLF/0,,contentMDK:21514122~menuPK:3875957~pagePK:210058~piPK:210062~theSitePK:515434,00.html">Trade Logistics Performance Index (LPI)</a> - World Bank site. &quot;The LPI is an interactive benchmarking tool created to help countries identify the challenges and opportunities they face in their performance on trade logistics and what  they can do to improve their performance – the LPI allow for comparisons across 150 countries.&quot; <br>
          <a href="http://r0.unctad.org/trains/tfori.htm">TRAINS on the Internet</a> - Online  access to the database on trade control measures (tariff, para-tariff and non-tariff measures) and on import flows (at Harmonized System 6-digit level.) <br>
          <a href="http://archive.unctad.org/Templates/webflyer.asp?docid=16171&intItemID=5772&lang=1">UNCTAD Handbook of Statistics Online</a> - Data on international merchandise trade and international trade in services. <br>
          <a href="http://www.itcdc.com/explore.php?p=12">USA  Trade Center</a> - Department of Commerce site links to Business Information Services for the Newly Independent States (BISNIS), Central and East European Business Information Center (CEEBIC), and Multilateral Development Bank Operations (MDBO). <br>
          <a href="http://www.wto.org/english/res_e/statis_e/statis_e.htm">World Trade Organization</a> - Trade statistics site with up-to-date aggregate developments in world trade. </div>


